<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kai Havertz is set to play alongside new team-mate Timo Werner for Germany against Spain tonight after German press claimed Bayer Leverkusen had accepted Chelsea's £89million bid. </p>

<p>The German sensation has been linked with a move to Stamford Bridge all summer and the club-record deal looks on the verge of completion. </p>

<p>The 21-year-old will line up for his national team against Spain in their Nations League clash against Spain and will offer Chelsea fans a taste of what to expect by starting with Werner.</p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Kai Havertz is set to play with Timo Werner for Germany ahead of his £90million Chelsea move</p>
